oc:kn_051af29b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing onboarding delivery format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Show, don't tell — demonstrate with working examples and real functionality rather than descriptions. Use interactive guidance over passive reading." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users learn by doing. Interactive onboarding produces higher comprehension and retention than passive instruction." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5b236049 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing onboarding flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never force users through long onboarding before they can use the product. Always provide a visible 'Skip' option and never show the same onboarding twice." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Blocking access frustrates users, especially experienced ones. Repeated onboarding creates annoyance and signals disrespect for user intelligence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_61253380 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any onboarding flow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Get users to their 'aha moment' as quickly as possible. Teach the 20% that delivers 80% of value, and save advanced features for contextual discovery." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Onboarding success is measured by time to value, not completeness of knowledge transfer. Users who reach value quickly become retained users." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_6a566ff7 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring onboarding content and feature discovery" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use progressive disclosure — teach one thing at a time, introduce 1-3 core concepts maximum upfront, and reveal complexity gradually as users encounter features." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Cognitive overload kills onboarding effectiveness. Users can only absorb a limited amount of new information per session." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a9aca97b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After implementing onboarding flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify onboarding quality by measuring: time to completion, comprehension, user action taken, skip rate, completion rate, and time to value." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Onboarding is an iterative process. Quantitative metrics reveal whether the design actually accelerates activation or needs simplification." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_aaa03ba4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any onboarding design work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before designing onboarding, identify the 'aha moment', understand user experience level, and ensure design context has been gathered via the Context Gathering Protocol." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Onboarding without a clear target outcome or user understanding will be generic and ineffective. Context ensures the onboarding is tailored to the actual product and audience." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c815a8d4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing empty states for any feature or section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design empty states as onboarding opportunities. Every empty state must answer: what will appear here, why it matters, and how to get started." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty states are the most overlooked onboarding touchpoint. Blank space is a missed opportunity to guide users toward their first action." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ef2f3970 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing any onboarding pattern with tooltips, tours, or announcements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Track onboarding completion state and respect user dismissals. Use LocalStorage or equivalent to persist 'seen' states so onboarding is never repeated for returning users." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Showing onboarding repeatedly is annoying and signals poor engineering. State persistence is essential for production onboarding." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

